chargeHist.descr: Tampering w/ a Global Positioning System Tracking Device

result.execSummary:
The defendant Eduardo Martinez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Tampering w/ a Global Positioning System Tracking Device, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.465(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

03:10 PM; Case called for Plea/sentencing hearing.  Defendant Eduardo Martinez in court, in custody at WCJ (on OTP from DCI), with attorney Amanda Marie Nimmer.   Kristi J Gordon appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court notes a plea questionnaire has been filed and recites the offer.  State and Defense confirm the offer.  Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1, Court finds defendant guilty of Count 1.  Court orders Counts 2 & 3 dismissed and read in.  Court orders defendant may be returned to DCI.

Sentencing arguments made by Atty. Gordon.
Sentencing arguments made by Atty. Nimmer.
Defendant presents statements.

COUNT 1:
The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed Sentence of:

3 Years Imprisonment (Consecutive to any other current sentence)
-	1 Year of Initial Confinement
-	2 Years of Extended Supervision

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
-	Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
-	Follow any conditions deemed appropriate by Agent;
-	No violent contact with Victim A.

COSTS:  $268.00;

DNA Surcharge: $250.00;

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  to be paid during term of imprisonment and during extended supervision. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.
	
Felony warnings, immigration warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
